The Cue

47
00:03:48,769 --> 00:03:52,680
Whenever you feel the urge for your habit,
ask yourself 1) what time it is, 2) where

48
00:03:52,680 --> 00:03:57,778
you are, 3) who else is around you, 4) what
you just did and 5) what emotions you are

49
00:03:57,778 --> 00:04:02,609
feeling. Atleast one of these is the cue for
your habit. Look for consistencies to spot

50
00:04:02,609 --> 00:04:08,849
them when wanting a cigarette, junk food,
drugs, video games, porn, what have you.

51
00:04:08,848 --> 00:04:12,058
The Reward
What craving are you satisfying?

52
00:04:12,058 --> 00:04:17,350
You've got to figure out how you can substitute
the harmful reward, with a neutral or positive

53
00:04:17,350 --> 00:04:22,360
reward that will still lead to satisfaction.
For heavy smokers there's things like nicotine

54
00:04:22,360 --> 00:04:27,300
chewing gum, called nicorette. By chewing
those instead of smoking you protect your

55
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:31,629
lungs, while still receiving that nicotine
your body has become addicted to. Now that

56
00:04:31,629 --> 00:04:35,939
is not ideal, since you're not fighting the
addiction, however it's better than breathing

57
00:04:35,939 --> 00:04:40,579
in harmful substances. There's also electronic
cigarettes that do less harm to your body,

58
00:04:40,579 --> 00:04:44,359
I'm not a doctor, so I don't know, but they
basically allow smokers to feel like they're

59
00:04:44,360 --> 00:04:49,430
smoking a normal cigarette, but as I mentioned
earlier, maybe the craving you're satisfying

60
00:04:49,430 --> 00:04:54,139
is that little buzz you get from a cigarette
that little high and you could try and substitute

61
00:04:54,139 --> 00:04:59,189
that with the high that you get from running
a few miles or doing a few pushups and situps.

62
00:04:59,189 --> 00:05:01,680
It does work.
The Routine

63
00:05:01,680 --> 00:05:06,389
Once you've identified the cue and the reward
you can insert a new routine. You choose an

64
00:05:06,389 --> 00:05:11,199
activity that is triggered by the old cue
and delivers the old reward. In my example,

65
00:05:11,199 --> 00:05:15,610
the whole cigarette isn't the reward, the
nicotine or "the act of smoking", or that

66
00:05:15,610 --> 00:05:20,430
little buzz is the reward. The new routine
then could be the nicotine chewing gums or

67
00:05:20,430 --> 00:05:24,009
the electronic cigarette that could help you,
but if you're really serious about quitting

68
00:05:24,009 --> 00:05:29,259
for good, you have to stop telling everybody
that "you're trying to quit" and tell them

69
00:05:29,259 --> 00:05:34,479
"you quit, that's it, you're a non-smoker"
and when you feel that urge for nicotine,

70
00:05:34,478 --> 00:05:38,860
